name: Tangerine & Chili Marinated Pitted Green Olives
description: Sugar, spice and everything nice! We love this unique pairing of buttery green olives with dried tangerine slices and fiery chili peppers. Serve with Prosecco and smoked almonds or finely dice and bake over wild salmon.

name: Taggiasca Olives
description: The celebrated olive of the Liguria region in the Italian Riviera, Taggiasca’s fruity flavor is the centerpiece of Italian fare. With a deep violet skin it offers a firm bite and a fruity and mildly sweet flavor. Its small size is perfect for snacking and its strong aroma and clean finish makes is perfect for making extra virgin olive oil. Frutto’s Taggiasca olives are packed in an herb infused oil that can be used for a great flavor or marinade or light dressing.

name: Sicilian Green Olives
description: The Sicilian green olive is a large sour tasting olive commonly marinated in herbs. They have a Kermit-green hue, meaty, buttery flesh, and a mild flavor. They May also be pitted.

name: Red Cerignola Olives
description: Imported from Apulia, Cerignolas are the largest olives in the world. Cerignolas have a fruity, mild, clean taste, but their most impressive feature is their size and resulting meatiness. Biting into a Cerignola is almost like biting into a plulm. Festive red in color, serve them as an appetizer with cocktails.

name: Pitted Taggiasca Olives
description: The Taggiasca olive, grown in Liguria, Italy, has a delicate flavor and fruity aroma. Pitted and preserved in extra virgin olive oil, these Taggiasca Olives are packed with flavor with an incomparable taste. These olives are perfect as part of an antipasto spread, or to use in pasta sauces, pizza, meat, fish or poultry dishes, or on sandwiches.

name: Pitted Kalamata Olives
